在 C++ 里，同一个符号在不同位置含义不同。在类型旁边写 T *p 表示 p 是指向 T 的指针；在类型旁边写 T &r 表示 r 是 T 的引用（另一个名字的别名）。在表达式里，一元 * 表示对指针解引用（得到它所指的对象）；

一元 & 表示取某个对象的地址（得到指针）。所以：声明里的 */& 说明“它是什么类型”；表达式里的 */& 说明“对已有变量做什么操作”。 

例子：

template <class type>
void swapIt(type &a, type &b)
{
    type temp = a;
    std::cout << "&temp = " << &temp << std::endl;
    std::cout << "&a = " << &a << std::endl;
    std::cout << "&b = " << &b << std::endl;
    a = b;
    b = temp;
}

int main()
{
    printHeader("Template Function Checks");

    int x = 2, y = 8;
    int *p = &x;
    int *q = &y;
    std::cout << "&x = " << &x << " and &y = " << &y << std::endl;
    std::cout << "&p = " << &p << " and &q = " << &q << std::endl;
    std::cout << "*p = " << *p << " and *q = " << *q << std::endl;
    std::cout << "p = " << p << " and q = " << q << std::endl;
    std::cout << "======================================= " << std::endl;
    swapIt(x, y);
    std::cout << "======================================= " << std::endl;
    std::cout << "&x = " << &x << " and &y = " << &y << std::endl;
    std::cout << "&p = " << &p << " and &q = " << &q << std::endl;
    std::cout << "*p = " << *p << " and *q = " << *q << std::endl;
    std::cout << "p = " << p << " and q = " << q << std::endl;
}

于是出来的结果是：

